title: Trapping Rain Water
description: The Trapping Rain Water problem is a classic algorithmic challenge. You are given an array of non-negative integers representing the height of each bar in a histogram where the width of each bar is 1. Your task is to compute how much water it can trap after raining.
input_format: A single line containing space-separated integers representing the heights.
output_format: Output a single integer representing the total amount of trapped water.
